    <chapter xml:id="sec-item-property-values">
        <title>Manifest <markup>item</markup> Properties</title>

        <para>The following tables define properties for use in the <markup>manifest</markup>
            <olink targetdoc="packages" targetptr="sec-item-elem" type="epub-spec">item element</olink>
            <olink targetdoc="packages" targetptr="attrdef-item-properties" type="epub-spec">properties
            attribute</olink>.</para>

        <para>The <emphasis role="strong">Applies to</emphasis> field indicates which Publication Resource type(s) the given
            property <literal role="rfc2119">may</literal> be specified on, the <emphasis role="strong"
                >Cardinality</emphasis> field indicates the number of times the property <literal role="rfc2119"
                >must</literal> appear within the Package Document scope, and the <emphasis role="strong">Usage</emphasis>
            field indicates usage conditions.</para>

        <section xml:id="sec-cover-image">
            <title>cover-image</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="cover-image" xreflabel="cover-image">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>cover-image</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">The <property>cover-image</property> property identifies the
                                described Publication Resource as the cover image for the Publication.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry>All <olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="tbl-core-media-types" type="epub-spec">raster and
                                    vector image types</olink></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Zero or one</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry>Optional.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="sec-mathml">
            <title>mathml</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="mathml" xreflabel="mathml">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>mathml</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">The <property>mathml</property> property indicates that the
                                described Publication Resource contains one or more instances of MathML markup.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry><olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub" type="epub-spec">EPUB
                                    Content Documents</olink></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Zero or more</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry><literal role="rfc2119">Must</literal> be set if and only if the criterion specified in
                                the description is met.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="sec-nav">
            <title>nav</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="nav" xreflabel="nav">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>nav</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">The <property>nav</property> property indicates that the
                                described Publication Resource constitutes the <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                    targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-nav" type="epub-spec">EPUB Navigation
                                    Document</olink> of the given <olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-rendition"
                                    type="epub-spec">Rendition</olink>.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry>The <olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-nav" type="epub-spec"
                                    >EPUB Navigation Document</olink>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Exactly one</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry>Required.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="sec-remote-resources">
            <title>remote-resources</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="remote-resources" xreflabel="remote-resources">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>remote-resources</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header multi-para">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">
                                <para>The <property>remote-resources</property> property indicates that the described
                                    Publication Resource contains one or more internal references to other Publication
                                    Resources that are located outside of the <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                        targetptr="gloss-container" type="epub-spec">EPUB Container</olink>.</para>
                                <para>Refer to <olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="sec-resource-locations" type="epub-spec"/>
                                    for more information.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry>All Publication Resources with the capability of internal referencing (e.g., <olink
                                    targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-xhtml" type="epub-spec">XHTML
                                    Content Documents</olink>, <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                    targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-svg" type="epub-spec">SVG Content
                                    Documents</olink>, CSS Style Sheets and <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                    targetptr="gloss-media-overlay-document" type="epub-spec">Media Overlay
                                Documents</olink>).</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Zero or more</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry><literal role="rfc2119">Must</literal> be set if and only if the criterion specified in
                                the description is met.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="sec-scripted">
            <title>scripted</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="scripted" xreflabel="scripted">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>scripted</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">The <property>scripted</property> property indicates that the
                                described Publication Resource is a <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                    targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-scripted" type="epub-spec">Scripted Content
                                    Document</olink> (i.e., contains scripted content and/or elements from HTML5
                                forms).</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry><olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub" type="epub-spec">EPUB
                                    Content Documents</olink></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Zero or more</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry><literal role="rfc2119">Must</literal> be set if and only if the criterion specified in
                                the description is met.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="sec-svg">
            <title>svg</title>
            <informaltable xml:id="svg" xreflabel="svg">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Name:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property">
                                <property>svg</property>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Description:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-desc">
                                <para>The <property>svg</property> property indicates that the described Publication Resource
                                    embeds one or more instances of SVG markup.</para>
                                <para>This property <literal role="rfc2119">must</literal> be set when SVG markup is included
                                    directly in the resource and <literal role="rfc2119">may</literal> be set when the SVG is
                                    referenced from the resource (e.g., from an <xref linkend="refHTML5"/>
                                    <markup>img</markup>, <markup>object</markup> or <markup>iframe</markup> element).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Applies to:</entry>
                            <entry><olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-xhtml" type="epub-spec"
                                    >XHTML Content Documents</olink>; the value is implied for <olink targetdoc="spec"
                                    targetptr="gloss-content-document-epub-svg" type="epub-spec">SVG Content
                                    Documents</olink>.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Cardinality:</entry>
                            <entry role="rdfa-cardinality">
                                <option>Zero or more</option>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry role="rdfa-property-header">Usage:</entry>
                            <entry><literal role="rfc2119">Must</literal> be set if and only if the criterion specified in
                                the description is met.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="manifest-item-properties-recursive">
            <title>Usage</title>
            <para>The <property>mathml</property>, <property>remote-resources</property>, <property>scripted</property> and
                    <property>switch</property> properties <literal role="rfc2119">must</literal> be specified whenever the
                resource referenced by an <markup>item</markup> matches their respective definitions. These properties do not
                apply recursively to content included into a resource (e.g., via the HTML5 <markup>iframe</markup> element).
                For example, if a non-scripted XHTML Content Document embeds a scripted Content Document, only the embedded
                document's manifest <markup>item</markup>
                <markup>properties</markup> attribute will have the <property>scripted</property> value. </para>
        </section>

